  "description": [
    "2 TELEGRAMS IN BRIEF WAR President McKinley has consented to appoint Gen Lew Wallace a major general The defenses of Caimanera were demolished by the Texas Marble head and Suwanee 001 William J Bryan appeared in Omaha on a visit of Inspection and recevled an ovation from the volun teers there An official note of the Madrid gov ernment denies the charge that Span ish soldiers mutilated our deal at Calmenera Latest indications are that an army of at least 18000 men will be sent to Porto Rico Havana cigars are no longer on the market The last consignment came by way of London Diplomats In Washington sa that the occupation of Cuba end all hope of a speedy peace The honorary degree of doctor of laws was conferred upon RearAd miral Dewey by Princeton The slate department at Washington word that the Cadiz fleet was still sailing eastward yesterday Admiral Dewey cabled to Washing ton that the Philippine Insurgeiiis treat their prisoners humanely Semiofficial advices from Berlin report that Germany will not inter fere with us in the Philippines The London Times prints a report that the insurgents have captured exGovOen Augustls family James T Gatewood private eec Telary"
